Select the sale_id and create a sales_period column. Use a CASE statement on the extracted hour from sale_date to show 'Morning' (before 12), 'Afternoon' (12-17), or 'Evening' (after 17)

Solution:

SELECT
sale_id,
CASE 
WHEN EXTRACT(HOUR FROM sale_date) < 12 THEN 'Morning'
WHEN EXTRACT(HOUR FROM sale_date) BETWEEN 12 AND 17 THEN 'Afternoon'
WHEN EXTRACT(HOUR FROM sale_date) > 17 THEN 'Evening'
ELSE NULL
END AS sales_period
FROM sales
